The paper deals with sequential decision-making problems and proposes a hybrid policy learning scheme that combines Direct Policy Search (DPS) and Look-Ahead Tree (LT) policies. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) which deals with decision-making problems, Machine Learning (cs.LG) which includes policy learning, Robotics (cs.RO) which involves decision-making in robotics, Systems and Control (cs.SY) which deals with control policies, and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) which includes tree-based algorithms.
